Rakuen's Canopy Workshop compact maintains Confluence Text sections through retained Circle-lineage
Sorcerer practitioners as operational reference, not scholarly archive. Sections covering atmospheric
interaction during ashfall, water-earth multi-school boundary effects during flooding, and
vegetation-fire interaction in forest-adjacent burns are preserved for disaster management use.
Rakuen has no Axiomatic academic presence and therefore no formal restriction on access. Garden
Ledger Clerks document Confluence Text consultations during two of four southern grain emergencies
